WEBVTT

00:07.466 --> 00:08.592
[DOOR CLOSES]

00:10.344 --> 00:12.551
You wanted to talk.

00:13.097 --> 00:14.212
Talk.

00:14.432 --> 00:19.472
This room, it's where I first called on you.

00:19.687 --> 00:23.805
-Where I met your grandmother, your brother.
-If you're feeling this nostalgic, Bill...

00:24.025 --> 00:25.811
...I gotta ask, what the fuck?

00:26.027 --> 00:30.487
Because to my mind,
nostalgia and suicide don't mix.

00:32.783 --> 00:35.160
You deserve everything, Sookie.

00:35.369 --> 00:36.529
You deserve the world.

00:36.746 --> 00:40.910
What if all I want right now
is to see you live?

00:41.125 --> 00:43.491
You have to look to your future.

00:44.045 --> 00:45.876
What does it look like with me in it?

00:46.088 --> 00:49.376
I don't wanna have this conversation.
We've been down this path before.

00:49.592 --> 00:52.459
That's because for us,
all roads lead to this path.

00:52.678 --> 00:54.384
How many times have you sworn me off?

00:54.597 --> 00:57.430
How many times have you promised yourself
no more vampires?

00:57.642 --> 00:59.132
And yet here we are again.

00:59.352 --> 01:05.097
You're choosing to die because I have no
self-respect? That makes a lot of sense.

01:05.316 --> 01:07.898
-That is not what I'm saying.
-Then what are you saying?

01:08.110 --> 01:12.023
Because I swear to God, I'm afraid
that you're gonna drop dead any minute...

01:12.240 --> 01:15.403
...and I'll never know why the fuck
you're doing this.

01:16.244 --> 01:17.654
Why are you doing this?

01:17.870 --> 01:20.486
This disease, Sookie...

01:21.958 --> 01:25.121
...it's made me feel more human
than I've ever felt before.

01:25.336 --> 01:27.873
Even when l was human.

01:28.089 --> 01:31.923
On the way over here tonight,
I stopped by my family's graves.

01:32.134 --> 01:36.218
Caroline's, Sarah's, Thomas's and mine.

01:37.556 --> 01:39.217
Mine is a lie.

01:39.684 --> 01:41.549
I should be with them.

01:41.769 --> 01:43.384
It's where I belong.

01:43.604 --> 01:45.981
-No.
-Sookie.

01:47.191 --> 01:50.058
We're born, we grow, and we learn...

01:50.278 --> 01:52.564
...and we have children.

01:53.239 --> 01:56.276
Maybe we get to meet
our children's children...

01:56.492 --> 02:00.076
...but then we pass on and that--
That is a life.

02:02.206 --> 02:06.415
And if we stayed together,
I would be denying you the best parts of that.

02:07.295 --> 02:08.375
Do you understand?

02:09.588 --> 02:11.328
Even just a little?

02:13.801 --> 02:14.836
Mm-hm.

02:16.804 --> 02:19.466
I've seen you around children...

02:19.765 --> 02:22.472
...seen how you light up around them.

02:23.811 --> 02:28.180
I would hate for you to never know what
that feels like, to have children of your own.

02:31.277 --> 02:33.893
Then why don't you just break up with me?

02:35.656 --> 02:38.693
If I can't swear you off,
why don't you swear me off?

02:38.909 --> 02:40.445
Because I can't.

02:42.455 --> 02:43.820
Because I love you too much.

02:49.462 --> 02:51.703
I want you to help me.

02:53.966 --> 02:55.581
Help you?

02:56.385 --> 02:58.922
What do you fairies call it?

02:59.430 --> 03:01.011
The ultimate kindness.

03:03.517 --> 03:05.132
What?

03:08.898 --> 03:10.638
You want me to kill you?

03:10.858 --> 03:12.314
Are you fucking kidding me?

03:12.526 --> 03:16.235
Use your light on me and you will be done
with vampires forever.

03:17.281 --> 03:21.069
If you don't, there's gonna be a line of suitors
from here to the gates of hell...

03:21.285 --> 03:23.571
...trying to call you theirs.

03:23.829 --> 03:25.820
Do you realize what you're asking me to do?

03:26.040 --> 03:29.828
Sookie, what you are is extraordinary.

03:30.044 --> 03:31.875
But so is being human.

03:32.088 --> 03:35.125
All I'm asking is the same question
that you've been asking...

03:35.341 --> 03:37.627
...every day since the first day that we met.

03:37.843 --> 03:40.129
It's what you've always wanted.

03:40.554 --> 03:42.806
A normal life.

03:44.683 --> 03:46.184
Show me the true death.

03:48.562 --> 03:50.939
And you'll be setting us both free.

03:51.690 --> 03:53.351
-I think you should go.
-Sweetheart—-

03:53.567 --> 03:55.819
Please don't make me
rescind your invitation.

04:07.331 --> 04:08.867
Will you at least think about it?

04:09.083 --> 04:13.372
Believe me, I'm thinking about it.

04:24.306 --> 04:25.512
[DOOR CLOSES]

05:58.025 --> 06:00.767
[TECHNO PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

06:08.244 --> 06:09.654
[SIGHS]

06:15.042 --> 06:17.499
I'm so sorry, Eric.

06:20.422 --> 06:22.083
Eric.

06:23.092 --> 06:25.003
-Unchain her.
-What?

06:25.219 --> 06:27.426
ERIC:
Unchain her, Pamela.

06:27.638 --> 06:30.630
PAM: Are you just winging it,
or do you have a plan here?

06:30.849 --> 06:32.760
-I'm setting her free.
-What?

06:32.977 --> 06:34.592
You are?

06:35.020 --> 06:37.932
If you don't want to do it,
I'll do it myself.

06:38.190 --> 06:39.396
[GASPS]

06:39.608 --> 06:40.848
SARAH:
Thank you.

06:41.068 --> 06:43.400
Oh, don't get too excited, sweetheart.

06:43.612 --> 06:45.148
We're gonna catch up with you.

06:45.364 --> 06:48.197
[SCREAMS THEN GRUNTS]

06:48.409 --> 06:51.446
In case you've forgotten, Eric,
the whole world's looking for her.

06:51.662 --> 06:54.028
If Gus doesn't know about the tunnel,
why not crawl out with her?

06:54.248 --> 06:57.661
Because, Pamela Swynford De Beaufort...

06:57.876 --> 06:59.582
...we are going to kill Mr. Gus.

07:00.462 --> 07:01.588
And we're gonna steal
New Blood from him.

07:01.880 --> 07:02.915
Unh!

07:03.132 --> 07:04.963
I've tried trusting, I've tried sharing.

07:05.175 --> 07:06.301
[GASPS]

07:07.011 --> 07:09.297
And it's just not fucking working for me.

07:10.889 --> 07:13.016
Now, are you with me or not?

07:13.225 --> 07:15.807
Oh, I am so fucking with you.

07:16.687 --> 07:18.268
I thought you might be.

07:22.151 --> 07:26.360
I'm gonna remove your gag, and you're
not gonna make a peep, understood?

07:29.617 --> 07:30.652
Attagirl.

07:37.166 --> 07:39.657
Now Pam's gonna feed you
some of her blood.

07:40.628 --> 07:41.788
Open your mouth.

07:42.004 --> 07:43.119
Unh.

07:47.301 --> 07:49.007
Now, with her blood inside you...

07:49.219 --> 07:53.178
...she can always find you,
so long as you're frightened.

07:56.393 --> 07:58.679
Are you frightened?

07:58.896 --> 07:59.931
[WHIMPERING]

08:00.606 --> 08:03.188
Good. You should be.

08:03.400 --> 08:08.861
Because wherever you go,
whoever you talk to, whatever you do...

08:09.073 --> 08:12.236
...everybody wants you dead.

08:14.787 --> 08:18.154
Which means that,
as much as Pamela and I hate you...

08:18.916 --> 08:21.874
...we're the best friends you got.

08:22.086 --> 08:29.083
So talk to no one, ﬁnd a safe place
and wait for her to ﬁnd you.

08:32.262 --> 08:34.048
ERIC: Mr. Gus!
PAM: Help!

08:34.264 --> 08:36.755
ERIC: Sarah escaped!
PAM: Help us!

08:41.980 --> 08:43.971
[GUNS COOKING]

08:44.483 --> 08:45.973
How'd she get out of here?

08:46.193 --> 08:47.399
There's a tunnel.

08:59.748 --> 09:01.579
-You let her go?
-We sure did.

09:01.750 --> 09:02.739
YELLS [lN JAPANESE]:

09:02.918 --> 09:04.078
Kill them!

09:05.295 --> 09:06.421
[GRUNTING]

09:08.465 --> 09:10.842
-Let him go.
-I thought you were gonna kill him.

09:13.137 --> 09:14.798
Humans are slow.

09:15.889 --> 09:17.004
[PANTING]

09:22.563 --> 09:23.643
[SCREAMS]

09:44.585 --> 09:45.574
[IN JAPANESE]

09:45.753 --> 09:48.290
My condolences, fellas.

09:48.964 --> 09:50.875
[YAKUZA SCREAMING]

09:53.469 --> 09:57.678
[ENGINE REVVING AND TIRES SCREECHING]

10:05.981 --> 10:07.187
[SIGHS]

10:07.399 --> 10:09.230
[TECHNO PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

10:36.804 --> 10:37.884
[GASPS]

10:38.096 --> 10:39.256
PAM:
There you are.

10:39.473 --> 10:42.886
Sarah Newlin eating garbage.

10:43.101 --> 10:45.012
Who'd have thunk it?

10:49.608 --> 10:51.144
You wanna know why I'm here?

10:51.902 --> 10:54.644
Sure, I'll bite. Why are you here?

10:55.113 --> 10:57.320
This is where Eric turned Willa.

10:58.492 --> 10:59.527
Question:

10:59.743 --> 11:01.734
If I didn't know that,
how come you do?

11:01.954 --> 11:04.286
It was in Bill Compton's book.

11:04.498 --> 11:07.035
Hmm. It was. Must've skipped that chapter.

11:07.251 --> 11:09.537
TO be honest, I kind of skimmed
the whole thing...

11:09.753 --> 11:12.210
...IOOking for the parts
that were about me.

11:16.635 --> 11:18.842
I'm a horrible person, aren't I?

11:20.264 --> 11:22.596
Yes, dear. You are.

11:24.852 --> 11:26.342
Which is Why I think...

11:26.562 --> 11:30.896
...I would make a kick-ass vampire.

11:31.984 --> 11:33.770
Don't you?

11:34.695 --> 11:38.187
-You're serious?
-As a heart attack.

11:38.657 --> 11:39.942
Will you turn me?

11:41.785 --> 11:44.367
Absolutely not.

11:44.580 --> 11:46.787
But I would work my ass off for you.

11:46.999 --> 11:48.785
I have spent my entire adult life...

11:49.001 --> 11:51.708
...trying to be the best woman
behind the man I could be...

11:51.920 --> 11:54.081
...and maybe the problem all along...

11:54.298 --> 11:57.461
...is I was meant to be the woman...

11:57.676 --> 11:59.257
...behind the woman.

12:00.470 --> 12:01.801
Ha-ha-ha.

12:02.890 --> 12:05.381
So you're just gonna be a lesbian now.

12:07.102 --> 12:10.720
If you made me a vampire, yes.

12:11.273 --> 12:14.140
I would do things for you.

12:15.152 --> 12:18.690
Or you could do things to me.

12:19.489 --> 12:21.946
However you wanna play it.

12:24.161 --> 12:26.573
I figured, since Tara's gone-- Unh!

12:26.788 --> 12:29.370
Don't you dare talk to me about Tara.

12:29.583 --> 12:31.244
DO you understand me?

12:31.460 --> 12:32.996
[GASPING]

12:39.468 --> 12:44.633
I wouldn't let you go down on me
for a billion dollars.

12:45.474 --> 12:48.637
And as for me going down on you...

12:49.061 --> 12:52.428
...there's not enough
money in the world.

12:52.648 --> 12:56.357
But there is one thing I want from you.

12:56.568 --> 12:57.978
What?

12:58.779 --> 13:00.895
Your blood.

13:01.114 --> 13:02.945
Aah!

13:03.158 --> 13:06.867
I haven't been vaccinated yet.

13:09.790 --> 13:13.999
[SARAH SCREAMING]

13:19.174 --> 13:22.086
[CAR APPROACHES]

13:23.595 --> 13:25.301
Jessica.

13:45.951 --> 13:47.316
Howdy, Vampire Bill.

13:47.536 --> 13:48.776
Hoyt Fortenberry.

13:48.996 --> 13:50.861
Thought you'd moved to Alaska.

13:52.749 --> 13:55.661
Yes, sir, I did, but I came back
for my mama's funeral.

13:55.877 --> 13:56.912
I know.

13:57.129 --> 13:58.869
I think I'm here to stay.

13:59.089 --> 14:02.377
Well, I for one am glad to hear it.

14:02.592 --> 14:05.425
Yeah.
Did you get that bag of blood I left for you?

14:05.637 --> 14:08.470
I did find a bag Of blood,
but I didn't know it was from you.

14:08.682 --> 14:11.549
I don't want you to die, Bill.

14:12.894 --> 14:15.021
That's what I came to say.

14:15.647 --> 14:18.229
-I know you don't, sweetheart.
JESSICA: But also...

14:25.907 --> 14:29.650
On the way over,
I thought about it...

14:30.620 --> 14:34.329
...and that's what I would want
to hear from me...

14:34.791 --> 14:36.577
...iflwas you.

14:39.046 --> 14:40.627
So that's what I came up with.

14:44.926 --> 14:47.542
I'm never gonna understand
why you're doing this...

14:47.763 --> 14:51.881
...but one way or another,
I'll figure out a way to accept it.

14:52.267 --> 14:53.632
[SIGHS]

14:53.935 --> 14:56.096
And I will, Bill.

14:56.646 --> 14:58.682
I will be Okay.

15:02.444 --> 15:04.355
BILL:
Thank you, Jess.

15:05.072 --> 15:07.734
That's exactly what I needed to hear.

15:12.537 --> 15:16.405
-You're warm.
-Yeah, I know.

15:19.252 --> 15:21.459
-Thank you for bringing her home.
-Yes, sir.

15:21.671 --> 15:23.662
And if there's anything
I can do for you....

15:25.801 --> 15:27.257
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

15:27.469 --> 15:29.881
Your decision to stay...

15:30.222 --> 15:34.556
...I assume that Jessica's
part of the reason for that?

15:35.977 --> 15:37.592
She's the whole reason.

15:41.399 --> 15:43.606
I apologize in advance
for being presumptuous...

15:43.819 --> 15:46.401
...but I guess as a dying man...

15:46.863 --> 15:48.569
...I get to take certain liberties.

15:51.451 --> 15:53.533
You think that you might...

15:54.079 --> 15:58.243
...one day get around
to asking Jessica to marry you?

15:59.126 --> 16:01.708
Whoa, Bill. Oh, my God.

16:01.920 --> 16:04.081
Hoyt, I'm so, so sorry.

16:04.297 --> 16:07.585
-NO, it's really early to be having those con--
-Yes, sir, I do.

16:10.011 --> 16:11.046
Mm-hm.

16:13.807 --> 16:16.014
What do you say, Jess?

16:16.476 --> 16:19.434
You wanna make an honest man
out of me one day?

16:19.813 --> 16:23.772
Hoyt, could I have a minute with Bill alone?

16:26.486 --> 16:28.442
We need to talk.

16:34.786 --> 16:37.994
-Jess, I'm sorry, but--
-Quiet.

16:39.166 --> 16:43.330
Just listen, Okay?

16:44.546 --> 16:48.130
I wish that I hadn't spent an embarrassingly
huge amount of my childhood...

16:48.341 --> 16:49.877
...dreaming about my wedding day.

16:50.093 --> 16:53.460
I wish that I was above all of that,
but I am not.

16:54.306 --> 16:59.266
I might be a vampire, Bill,
but I am also a girl.

17:01.188 --> 17:03.725
And what just happened down there...

17:03.940 --> 17:06.647
...isn't anything like what I dreamed about.

17:08.737 --> 17:09.772
Jess, he loves you.

17:09.988 --> 17:12.024
He doesn't know me.

17:12.282 --> 17:14.523
His memories of me start yesterday.

17:14.743 --> 17:18.406
That's more than enough time
to fall in love with someone.

17:18.622 --> 17:21.534
When it's real, it can happen in an instant.

17:21.750 --> 17:23.581
[G RU NTS]

17:29.883 --> 17:31.623
May I explain myself?

17:33.845 --> 17:34.880
You can try.

17:35.680 --> 17:36.931
[CLEARS THROAT]

17:45.774 --> 17:51.644
I'd already been made vampire
before my human daughter Sarah got wed.

17:53.949 --> 17:58.613
So it goes without saying
that I didn't get to give her away.

18:00.288 --> 18:03.075
Never even met the man she married.

18:12.342 --> 18:14.207
But it's not gonna be very long.

18:16.054 --> 18:18.261
And I guess I....

18:19.641 --> 18:23.225
I just wanted to know
that you'd be spoken for...

18:23.687 --> 18:26.178
...before I leave this place.

18:32.779 --> 18:34.360
Could I get a hug?

18:35.407 --> 18:37.523
Of course you can.

18:45.625 --> 18:47.240
Bill?

18:49.796 --> 18:54.130
Would you mind waiting up here...

18:54.342 --> 18:56.173
...while Hoyt and I have a little talk?

18:58.221 --> 18:59.677
What are you gonna tell him?

19:03.518 --> 19:07.978
That if he does really want to marry me...

19:11.067 --> 19:13.103
...I wonder if it could be today.

19:21.995 --> 19:24.953
[THUNDER RUMBLING
AND RAIN PATTERING]

19:37.802 --> 19:44.173
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

19:45.310 --> 19:49.349
YOUNG SOOKIE: Tara, wait up!
YOUNG TARA: I can't! Why don't you hurry up?

19:49.564 --> 19:52.306
YOUNG SOOKIE:
Because it's too slippery.

19:54.402 --> 19:57.018
Wait up! You're too fast!

19:57.238 --> 19:58.273
[LAUGHING]

19:58.490 --> 20:02.699
If the rain did to your hair what it does to mine,
you'd be fast, too.

20:10.752 --> 20:11.787
[DOOR CLOSES]

20:12.003 --> 20:14.836
GRAN:
Oh, dear. Now, you Sit down.

20:15.048 --> 20:16.959
How many times have I told you girls...

20:17.175 --> 20:20.042
...when you get caught in the rain
like that...

20:20.261 --> 20:22.638
...you call me and I'll come and pick you up?

20:22.847 --> 20:24.678
Come on, Gran. It was fun.

20:24.891 --> 20:27.052
Plus, we get hot chocolate this way.

20:27.936 --> 20:30.643
Oh, you got me figured out, do you?

20:30.855 --> 20:31.890
YOUNG TARA:
Mm-hm.

20:32.107 --> 20:33.142
[GRANLAUGHS]

20:33.358 --> 20:34.723
Thanks, Miss Stackhouse.

20:36.361 --> 20:39.945
-You're both welcome.
-Thank you, Gran.

20:40.156 --> 20:44.024
I'm gonna go fetch y'all some clothes.
Back in a jiff.

20:47.705 --> 20:50.538
YOUNG TARA:
Wonder when jason 's gonna get home.

20:50.875 --> 20:53.912
Hope Miss S tackhouse
pick out something cute for me.

20:54.087 --> 20:55.167
You like Jason?

20:55.380 --> 20:57.996
Stay out of my head, Sookie Stackhouse!

20:58.216 --> 21:00.127
I'm sorry, I can't help it.

21:00.343 --> 21:03.210
-It ain't fair.
-I said I'm sorry.

21:04.222 --> 21:05.678
Who do you like?

21:05.890 --> 21:07.175
I don't like anybody.

21:07.392 --> 21:10.634
You know my secret.
You have to tell me yours.

21:10.854 --> 21:13.470
Ifl liked anybody, I would...

21:14.566 --> 21:16.147
...but boys are nasty.

21:16.359 --> 21:17.724
They think nasty thoughts.

21:17.944 --> 21:20.902
So you don't ever wanna get married
and have a family?

21:21.114 --> 21:23.981
Of course I do, but I don't see how
I'm ever going to, is all.

21:24.200 --> 21:27.488
Stop it! I don't want to hear you
talking like that.

21:27.704 --> 21:29.865
You can have any kind of life you want.

21:30.081 --> 21:32.197
You can persevere.

21:32.417 --> 21:36.581
Anything you want, Sookie,
you are entitled to it.

21:36.796 --> 21:41.631
There are no limits on you
if you don't put them on yourself.

21:43.636 --> 21:47.299
I need to know that you understand me.

21:49.517 --> 21:50.757
I understand.

21:53.646 --> 21:57.104
If I'm not around, you hold her to it, Tara.

21:57.525 --> 21:58.685
Would you do that for me?

21:59.152 --> 22:00.688
Yes, Miss Stackhouse.

22:14.501 --> 22:15.911
[KNOCKING]

22:22.550 --> 22:23.585
Oh.

22:23.801 --> 22:27.589
Hi. Um, is Jason here?
I'm his sister, Sookie.

22:27.805 --> 22:30.296
I'm Brigette. It's nice to meet you. Heh.

22:30.517 --> 22:31.552
Likewise.

22:31.768 --> 22:35.886
-So Jason's still sleeping, but, um, come on in.
-Thanks.

22:40.693 --> 22:44.777
I'm sorry if this is awkward,
but, um, I kind of need to speak to him.

22:45.782 --> 22:47.147
Why should it be awkward?

22:47.617 --> 22:49.983
Because you're wearing
his boxers and whatnot.

22:50.745 --> 22:51.780
Oh.

22:51.996 --> 22:55.033
-We didn't sleep together or anything. Heh.
-Seriously?

22:55.208 --> 22:58.245
BRIGETTE: Broke up with Hoyt last night.
Can 't believe she thinks I 'd do that.

22:58.336 --> 22:59.746
DO you know Hoyt?

22:59.879 --> 23:03.872
Although, I '11 be damned ifjason
isn't the sweetest man I ever met.

23:04.342 --> 23:07.709
You're Hoyt's girlfriend from Alaska?

23:09.597 --> 23:11.633
Up till last night I was, yeah.

23:12.809 --> 23:13.844
Should I not ask?

23:17.188 --> 23:19.179
DO you want to wake him up or should I?

23:19.399 --> 23:21.390
Oh, you don't wake Jason up
without coffee.

23:21.609 --> 23:24.351
I looked in his cupboards,
but all I could find was instant.

23:24.571 --> 23:26.653
That's because he's disgusting.

23:31.411 --> 23:33.026
SOONE:
Jason?

23:33.538 --> 23:36.871
Wake up. I got coffee.

23:41.546 --> 23:44.709
-Careful, it's hot.
-What's going on?

23:47.677 --> 23:49.008
It's Bill.

23:49.220 --> 23:52.508
He asked me to kill him with my light ball.

23:54.601 --> 23:55.761
What the hell?

23:55.977 --> 24:02.189
He says he wants me to have a normal life
with kids and everything.

24:02.775 --> 24:04.686
But with him in the world, I never will.

24:05.069 --> 24:06.149
Wow.

24:07.905 --> 24:10.817
-What are you thinking?
-I don't know what to think.

24:11.284 --> 24:13.696
He looks so sick.

24:13.911 --> 24:15.822
And I feel so awful.

24:16.914 --> 24:19.496
I mean, he deserves
to be put out Of his misery...

24:19.709 --> 24:25.170
...and lord knows I've been back and forth
on this so many times, I can't count.

24:25.381 --> 24:27.838
ls being what I am...

24:28.051 --> 24:29.962
...a curse or a blessing?

24:30.762 --> 24:34.505
But now that somebody's
actually asking me to give it up...

24:36.434 --> 24:38.470
...I ain't so sure that I want to.

24:38.686 --> 24:40.802
And even then...

24:41.272 --> 24:44.309
...I ain't sure that I could...

24:44.692 --> 24:47.809
...even if I did know I wanted to.

24:50.573 --> 24:53.815
-Sook, are you--?
-What?

24:54.702 --> 24:57.079
Are you asking for advice from me?

24:58.122 --> 25:00.158
NO, not really.

25:00.375 --> 25:03.538
Good, because I got no idea
what to tell you to do.

25:04.128 --> 25:05.993
But I can promise you this.

25:06.214 --> 25:08.671
I will love you either way.

25:08.883 --> 25:10.714
I love you too.

25:10.927 --> 25:12.133
[CELL PHONE CHIMES]

25:12.345 --> 25:14.586
-Oh, that's me.
BRIGETTE: I'll get it!

25:15.098 --> 25:16.713
[CELL PHONE CHIMING]

25:19.352 --> 25:20.387
[SIGHS]

25:20.603 --> 25:21.638
Son of a bitch.

25:22.063 --> 25:24.554
-Uh, that's Brigette.
-Yeah, we met.

25:24.816 --> 25:27.228
Um, Jason? It's Hoyt.

25:27.902 --> 25:29.438
Thanks.

25:34.117 --> 25:35.152
Hoyt?

25:35.368 --> 25:39.907
Listen, I got kind of a strange question for you,
considering how we left things last night.

25:40.164 --> 25:41.199
Jessica said we were...

25:41.416 --> 25:43.122
JESSICA: Hey, uh, SOOk?
-Jessica?

25:43.334 --> 25:45.120
JESSICA:
Jason already on the phone with Hoyt?

25:45.336 --> 25:46.746
Don't even worry about it, man.

25:48.589 --> 25:50.329
Will you be my best man?

25:51.592 --> 25:52.923
Your best man?

25:53.177 --> 25:58.638
Um, you wouldn't happen to have anything that
could pass for, um, a wedding dress, would you?

25:59.600 --> 26:02.558
What the hell went on last night?

26:11.446 --> 26:14.563
-You ready, green thumb?
-Oh, yeah.

26:14.782 --> 26:16.067
Oh, here, let me.

26:16.284 --> 26:18.115
-Oh, thanks.
-I gotcha.

26:18.327 --> 26:21.069
-Throw those in the trunk?
-Uh, back seat.

26:25.877 --> 26:27.663
Sook, listen, uh...

26:28.045 --> 26:29.956
...I know today....

26:30.631 --> 26:33.589
Well, it's gotta be a tough day
to be going to a wedding.

26:34.719 --> 26:35.879
Doesn't matter.

26:36.095 --> 26:38.882
If Jessica wants to do this for Bill...

26:39.098 --> 26:41.555
...then I'm damn well
gonna do it for both of them.

26:43.060 --> 26:44.891
Mind holding these?

27:04.040 --> 27:08.875
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING ON SPEAKERS]

27:13.299 --> 27:16.086
Well, I ain't never been
to a vampire wedding before.

27:16.302 --> 27:18.213
Well, there's a first time
for everything.

27:18.429 --> 27:20.761
ARLENE: Did they say why they were getting
hitched so fast?

27:20.973 --> 27:24.557
Nope, all they said was could I perform
the ceremony, to come on over.

27:24.769 --> 27:26.475
She can't be pregnant, can she?

27:26.687 --> 27:29.599
Oh, I don't think so.
But wouldn't that be cool if she was?

27:29.816 --> 27:30.805
Cute little baby vamp.

27:30.983 --> 27:33.235
ARLENE: Tiny teeth.
HOLLY: Breastfeeding would be a bitch.

27:33.444 --> 27:34.479
ARLENE:
Uh, yeah.

27:34.695 --> 27:37.778
BILL: Sheriff Bellefleur?
-Yeah, Vampire Bill?

27:37.990 --> 27:40.197
BILL:
Is the front door closed?

27:43.120 --> 27:45.076
It is now.

27:45.373 --> 27:48.240
BILL: Would you mind
having a word with me in my office?

27:48.459 --> 27:51.246
Course. Hopefully this won't take too long.

27:51.462 --> 27:52.497
Don't worry about us.

27:52.713 --> 27:55.876
Oh, no, no. We'll just be snooping. Ha-ha-ha.

27:58.803 --> 28:02.170
ARLENE:
I just love how fancy it is.

28:02.390 --> 28:03.755
Take a seat.

28:08.479 --> 28:11.767
I heard you were sick,
but, uh, I didn't expect it to be this bad.

28:11.983 --> 28:13.143
Please.

28:17.989 --> 28:19.229
[SIGHS]

28:19.615 --> 28:21.901
I need to ask you a favor.

28:22.118 --> 28:23.608
Okay.

28:24.579 --> 28:27.946
Like you said,
there's a lot of history between us...

28:28.416 --> 28:30.281
...not all of it good.

28:30.501 --> 28:34.244
Legally speaking,
with your grandmother not fit and all...

28:34.839 --> 28:37.376
...you're my eldest remaining heir.

28:38.384 --> 28:40.921
We're family, remember? You and I.

28:41.637 --> 28:43.377
I remember.

28:44.265 --> 28:47.849
When I found out I was unwell,
I went to see an attorney...

28:48.269 --> 28:51.727
...see if I could
will my home to Jessica.

28:52.315 --> 28:55.523
It's kind Of a long story,
but it turns out that I can't.

28:55.735 --> 28:59.523
Which means that when I die
this house will pass over to you.

29:00.823 --> 29:01.938
[STAMMERS]

29:02.158 --> 29:04.695
I can't accept this house.

29:04.911 --> 29:06.276
For all kinds of reasons.

29:07.663 --> 29:10.871
I'm asking if you will rent it
to Jessica and Hoyt...

29:11.792 --> 29:14.955
...for the sum of one dollar a month.

29:16.088 --> 29:19.421
And if, for whatever reason,
they forget to pay...

29:19.800 --> 29:22.587
...maybe you can look away.

29:25.014 --> 29:27.505
Copy that, Vampire Bill.

29:29.143 --> 29:31.099
Consider it done.

29:31.812 --> 29:33.552
[KNOCKING]

29:39.153 --> 29:40.188
[CLICKS TONGUE]

29:42.031 --> 29:44.488
JASON: On this side.
-Yep.

29:46.535 --> 29:48.196
Like that?

29:50.665 --> 29:52.826
Brigette still at your place?

29:54.168 --> 29:56.204
[SIGHS]
Yeah.

29:57.546 --> 30:01.084
She, uh-- She leaves tonight.

30:02.510 --> 30:05.252
When you left for here,
you tell her where you were going?

30:07.306 --> 30:08.716
[SIGHS]

30:09.934 --> 30:11.219
Imean....

30:13.187 --> 30:16.679
I feel like shit. You think maybe
I should call her and say, you know, I'm--

30:16.899 --> 30:19.982
That right there is a terrible fucking idea,
is what that is.

30:21.570 --> 30:22.605
Sorry about your eye.

30:22.822 --> 30:25.108
And I'm sorry about your tie.
Come here, man.

30:30.746 --> 30:36.537
If taking a hit from a heavyweight is the price
I had to pay to get you back in my life...

30:36.961 --> 30:41.125
...I'd take one every day of the week
and twice on Sunday.

30:42.925 --> 30:44.586
There you go.

30:45.302 --> 30:46.508
Heh.

30:49.223 --> 30:50.258
I'm just....

30:50.766 --> 30:52.597
I'm starting to freak out a little bit.

30:52.810 --> 30:57.349
Well, if it makes you feel any better,
I'm pretty sure this ceremony ain't exactly legal.

30:57.982 --> 30:59.392
Aww....

30:59.942 --> 31:03.434
I seen this Old movie, Regarding Henry.

31:03.654 --> 31:09.695
And, uh, Harrison Ford
plays, uh, a big city lawyer guy named Henry.

31:09.910 --> 31:13.619
And when he gets into some kind of accident,
I can't remember what...

31:13.831 --> 31:16.322
...but he gets amnesia...

31:16.542 --> 31:20.126
...and, uh, he has to relearn everything.

31:20.337 --> 31:22.498
He don't even know the people in his life.

31:23.466 --> 31:25.752
Man, I feel just like Henry.

31:27.762 --> 31:29.093
He was shot.

31:29.305 --> 31:30.715
Who? Who was?

31:30.931 --> 31:32.796
-Henry.
-You saw it too.

31:33.017 --> 31:36.180
Well, we rented it together.

31:37.730 --> 31:39.345
HOYT:
You see?

31:39.815 --> 31:42.648
I want you to listen to me, Hoyt.

31:43.110 --> 31:46.227
It's been a long fucking week,
and it's been a weird fucking week...

31:46.447 --> 31:49.314
...but I've figured something out
along the way.

31:49.867 --> 31:52.779
We gotta live every day
like it's our last, man.

31:53.704 --> 31:55.035
And if we do that...

31:55.247 --> 31:58.284
...it puts everything in prescription for us.

31:59.919 --> 32:04.162
If I was to tell you
the world was gonna end tomorrow...

32:05.132 --> 32:06.872
...who would wanna wake up next to?

32:07.802 --> 32:09.338
Jessica. Mm-hm.

32:10.805 --> 32:13.638
Don't that tell you
everything you need to know?

32:14.100 --> 32:15.180
Yeah.

32:15.392 --> 32:17.178
Then get the hell out there, man.

32:17.394 --> 32:20.056
Let's go out there
and make some new memories.

32:20.689 --> 32:22.725
Let me help you here, man.

32:22.942 --> 32:25.274
Let's do this shit, Bubba.

32:25.486 --> 32:26.817
Let's do this shit.

32:27.488 --> 32:28.819
Let's do it.

32:38.541 --> 32:41.328
Fucking A.

32:51.178 --> 32:52.213
JESSICA:
Yeah?

32:52.429 --> 32:55.466
They sent me up here to see
if y'all were just about ready.

32:55.683 --> 32:58.095
SOOKIE:
Um, just putting on the final details.

32:58.310 --> 32:59.345
Two minutes.

32:59.562 --> 33:02.053
-Can I see her?
JESSICA: I could really use another set of eyes.

33:02.273 --> 33:04.264
-Why, you don't trust me?
JESSICA: NO, I trust you.

33:04.483 --> 33:05.598
-It's just--
-I'm kidding.

33:05.818 --> 33:06.978
[GASPS]

33:07.194 --> 33:10.778
Oh, girl, you don't need another minute.

33:10.990 --> 33:13.106
You're perfect.

33:15.077 --> 33:17.238
HOYT: Yes, sir, I do.
-Here they come!

33:20.040 --> 33:23.703
[CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYS
OVER SPEAKERS]

33:26.088 --> 33:28.795
-Everything all right?
SOOKIE: Jessica was just wondering...

33:29.008 --> 33:31.249
...if you felt up to
walking her down the aisle.

33:32.094 --> 33:33.174
Of course.

33:33.721 --> 33:34.927
She's in the foyer.

33:46.609 --> 33:48.349
Oh, Jess.

33:55.910 --> 33:58.242
You look so beautiful.

34:11.800 --> 34:14.257
[WOMEN GASPING]

34:20.976 --> 34:22.967
JASON:
You got this.

34:28.609 --> 34:31.351
[CLASSICAL MUSIC
CONTINUES PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

34:31.570 --> 34:32.730
Are you sure you're Okay?

34:32.947 --> 34:34.483
I'm okay. I'm great.

34:34.698 --> 34:36.438
Okay.

34:41.580 --> 34:43.821
Arlene, would you mind
turning down the music?

34:44.041 --> 34:45.076
Oh, shit, I forgot.

34:45.292 --> 34:47.408
[LAUGHING]

34:47.628 --> 34:49.289
[MUSIC STOPS]

34:51.382 --> 34:53.293
ARLENE:
I am so sorry. Go ahead, y'all.

34:56.929 --> 34:59.545
I, uh, I brought some notes
so I don't mess this up.

34:59.765 --> 35:01.881
I hope y'all don't mind.

35:05.896 --> 35:06.976
Please, be seated.

35:10.859 --> 35:12.440
We are all gathered here today...

35:12.653 --> 35:17.568
...to celebrate the relationship
of Jessica Hamby and Hoyt Fortenberry...

35:18.617 --> 35:21.154
...and to be witnesses and supporters...

35:21.370 --> 35:23.611
...of the commitment
they share with one another.

35:23.831 --> 35:26.994
Together we're a group
of the most important people in their lives...

35:27.209 --> 35:29.700
...and they've brought us here
to publicly recognize...

35:29.920 --> 35:33.583
...that we've all played a special part
in the love that they share today.

35:36.093 --> 35:39.005
Who gives Jessica away
in marriage to this man?

35:40.014 --> 35:41.629
I do.

35:49.481 --> 35:51.437
[SNIFFLES]

35:51.650 --> 35:53.857
JESSICA: NO, don't go.
-|'|| be sitting right here.

35:54.611 --> 35:56.442
I'm right behind you.

35:57.489 --> 36:00.196
ANDY: It's a beautiful thing,
fathers and daughters.

36:00.409 --> 36:02.946
BILL:
So happy. So much pain.

36:03.162 --> 36:04.902
Don ’t let them see.

36:05.122 --> 36:08.080
Be here. Be present.

36:08.542 --> 36:09.292
So happy.

36:10.210 --> 36:10.710
[GASPS]

36:11.337 --> 36:12.497
What?

36:12.713 --> 36:13.953
Nothing.

36:14.506 --> 36:15.666
You all right?

36:16.675 --> 36:18.336
I'm fine.

36:19.887 --> 36:24.472
BILL: I love you, Sookie Stackhouse.
I love you with everything I ’m made of.

36:24.767 --> 36:27.133
ANDY: Who gives Hoyt away
in marriage to this woman?

36:27.353 --> 36:29.309
Uh, I do.

36:29.521 --> 36:32.388
But Hoyt and me, we already hugged it out,
so you carry on, Father.

36:32.608 --> 36:33.643
[ALL LAUGHING]

36:33.859 --> 36:37.317
ANDY: Before we move on to the vows,
I just want to say one thing.

36:37.738 --> 36:40.980
The state of Louisiana,
the United States of America...

36:41.200 --> 36:43.407
...may not recognize this union...

36:43.660 --> 36:45.821
...but for my money...

36:46.038 --> 36:48.404
...there ain't a doubt
in my mind that God does.

36:49.041 --> 36:51.953
The love you two share is beautiful.

36:52.628 --> 36:54.459
And love is love...

36:55.255 --> 36:56.711
...plain and simple.

36:57.216 --> 36:58.251
Amen.

36:59.093 --> 37:02.802
ANDY: Uh, have y'all written down any thoughts
you wanna share with one another?

37:03.013 --> 37:05.425
[STAMMERING] The thing is,
there wasn't really much time.

37:05.641 --> 37:08.633
-It's Okay, I didn't write anything down either.
-Thank God.

37:08.852 --> 37:11.264
What about rings? DO you have any?

37:12.022 --> 37:13.523
I ain't got no ring.

37:13.732 --> 37:15.768
It's all good. We'll improvise.

37:17.820 --> 37:19.811
Hoyt, please, take Jessica's hand...

37:20.489 --> 37:22.400
...and repeat after me.

37:22.616 --> 37:27.451
I give you my heart as a symbol of our love.

37:29.039 --> 37:32.748
I give you my heart as a symbol of our love.

37:32.960 --> 37:35.793
ANDY: For today and tomorrow
and for all the days to come.

37:36.004 --> 37:38.086
HOYT: For today, tomorrow,
and all the days to come.

37:38.090 --> 37:41.127
BILL:
I want this for you so badly.

37:41.593 --> 37:43.754
So badly for you to have this.

37:44.430 --> 37:47.638
Please, Sookie. Set yourself free.

37:47.850 --> 37:49.841
AN DY:
Jessica, repeat after me.

37:50.060 --> 37:53.018
I give you my heart as a symbol of our love.

37:53.230 --> 37:56.688
I give you my heart as a symbol of our love.

37:56.900 --> 38:00.063
ANDY: For today--
-For today and tomorrow and tomorrow night...

38:00.279 --> 38:04.022
...and all Of the nights to come,
and we had really better hurry this thing up...

38:04.241 --> 38:06.448
-...because I am running out of tissues.
SOOKIE: On it.

38:07.453 --> 38:08.989
Thank you.

38:09.204 --> 38:12.196
ANDY: And know that my love is present
even when I am not.

38:12.416 --> 38:15.908
And know that my love is present
even when I am not.

38:16.128 --> 38:19.461
ANDY:
Okay, good, you two are almost hitched.

38:19.673 --> 38:21.834
Jessica, do you take this man
to be your husband?

38:22.050 --> 38:24.336
DO you promise to love him,
honor and keep him...

38:24.553 --> 38:27.920
...in sickness and in health,
and forsaking all others...

38:28.140 --> 38:31.678
...be faithful to him,
as long as you both shall live?

38:31.894 --> 38:34.180
-I do.
ANDY: Hoyt, do you take this woman...

38:34.396 --> 38:35.511
...to be your wife?

38:35.731 --> 38:37.972
DO you promise to love her,
honor and keep her...

38:38.192 --> 38:40.808
...in sickness and in health,
and forsaking all others...

38:41.028 --> 38:43.485
...be faithful to her,
as long as you both shall live?

38:44.031 --> 38:45.771
-I do.
ANDY: Excellent.

38:45.991 --> 38:49.154
I now pronounce you husband and wife.

38:49.369 --> 38:52.156
You may kiss your vampire bride.

38:53.040 --> 38:54.246
[CLAPPING AND CHEERING]

38:54.458 --> 38:56.665
JASON:
Bubba, congratulations.

39:08.013 --> 39:09.514
Sook...

39:10.224 --> 39:11.259
...are you all right?

39:11.475 --> 39:15.343
Because, uh, you ain't said
a word since Bill's house.

39:16.480 --> 39:18.266
I could hear Bill's thoughts.

39:19.775 --> 39:22.517
-Huh?
-I could hear him, Jason.

39:23.195 --> 39:24.560
I could hear him thinking.

39:25.239 --> 39:27.150
What the fuck?

39:27.616 --> 39:29.857
-I thought that wasn't even possible.
-So did I.

39:30.077 --> 39:32.784
But last night he was saying
how this disease...

39:32.996 --> 39:37.490
...is making him feel
more human than he's ever felt before.

39:37.960 --> 39:40.417
Guess he didn't know how right he was.

39:44.049 --> 39:47.132
Well, what did--? What was he thinking?

39:49.054 --> 39:50.794
All the right things.

39:51.014 --> 39:55.132
Everything that you want somebody
who loves you to be thinking about you.

39:56.144 --> 39:57.645
Except for the part about him...

39:57.854 --> 40:01.062
-...still wanting to die at your hand. Um....
-Yeah, except for that.

40:01.483 --> 40:03.724
Can you just give us a sweet little second?

40:03.944 --> 40:06.151
-Oh, yeah, sure.
-Thanks. Uh.

40:06.863 --> 40:08.239
She's sweet on you, you know.

40:09.491 --> 40:12.233
-NO, no, she ain't.
-I was listening to her this morning.

40:12.452 --> 40:14.488
Sook, I don't wanna hear it.

40:14.705 --> 40:17.287
Can Ijust say one thing
and then I'll shut up?

40:17.499 --> 40:20.161
-I swear.
-GO on.

40:21.587 --> 40:24.795
I get that you've got
some kind of personal growth story...

40:25.007 --> 40:26.963
...going on in your head about all this...

40:27.175 --> 40:30.133
...but if you were to somehow
wind up sleeping with her...

40:30.345 --> 40:31.721
...on the way to the airport--

40:31.930 --> 40:33.761
NO way, no how.

40:33.974 --> 40:37.637
I'm just gonna put her on the plane.
That's it.

40:37.853 --> 40:41.391
I'm just saying, if you do...

40:41.940 --> 40:43.521
...I approve.

40:44.610 --> 40:47.226
I like her, and I think you do too.

40:49.489 --> 40:51.571
I ain't gonna be no girlfriend-fucker again.

40:52.826 --> 40:54.942
I get that...

40:55.162 --> 40:59.121
...but we just came from Hoyt's wedding.

40:59.333 --> 41:00.994
She ain't his girlfriend anymore.

41:03.754 --> 41:06.996
SOOKIE: SO nice to meet you.
-You too, Sookie.

41:08.675 --> 41:10.211
SOOKIE:
Bye, Brigette.

41:11.136 --> 41:12.467
BRIGETTE:
Thank you.

41:13.221 --> 41:14.882
[JASON CLEARS THROAT]

41:17.017 --> 41:19.599
-You ready?
-Hmm. . ..

41:20.395 --> 41:22.351
Yeah, put that on.

41:51.134 --> 41:52.965
Reverend Daniels?

41:55.055 --> 41:56.215
Miss Stackhouse?

41:57.015 --> 41:58.471
Is it okay if I come in?

41:59.184 --> 42:00.924
Of course it is, sweetheart.

42:05.607 --> 42:08.314
-What are you working on?
-This week's sermon.

42:09.236 --> 42:10.817
DO you always write in church?

42:11.279 --> 42:12.564
Not always.

42:12.781 --> 42:13.816
[SIGHS]

42:14.032 --> 42:16.990
But when the words don't want
to come out, I come in here to think.

42:17.202 --> 42:19.238
It makes me feel...

42:19.705 --> 42:21.320
...closer to God.

42:22.582 --> 42:23.742
Does he talk to you?

42:23.959 --> 42:27.292
-Not once.
-That's a shame.

42:27.504 --> 42:29.995
Because I could really use
his advice right about now.

42:33.260 --> 42:36.844
Well, when you got in your car
and drove over here...

42:37.055 --> 42:40.138
...now, you didn't expect
to find God sitting here, did you?

